<!--PageTitleFmt-->
        <div id='wikititle'>
          <div class='pagegroup'><a href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki'>PmWiki</a> /</div>
          <h1 class='pagetitle'>UTF-8</h1></div>
<!--PageText-->
<div id='wikitext'>
<p>
<a name='trailstart' id='trailstart'></a> 
</p><div style='clear:right;' >
</div>
<p>Summary: Enabling UTF-8 Unicode language encoding in your wiki. 
</p>
<p class='vspace'>UTF-8 supports all languages and alphabets, including Asian languages and their character depth. It is a widely supported and flexible character encoding. 
</p>
<p class='vspace'>It&rsquo;s fairly simple to enable UTF-8 on your wiki pages. Current PmWiki versions have the UTF-8 file which is enabled by default in the sample-config.php.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h2>Enabling UTF-8 on a new wiki</h2>
<p>If you start a new wiki in any language with the latest PmWiki version, it is highly recommended to enable UTF-8. In the future, PmWiki will change to use the UTF-8 encoding by default, so if you already use it, you will not need a complex &ldquo;migration&rdquo; to UTF-8 later.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>To enable UTF-8 for a new wiki, add this line near the beginning of config.php (the docs/sample-config.php file has this line already):
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><pre> include_once(&ldquo;scripts/xlpage-utf-8.php&rdquo;);
</pre><p class='vspace'>This line should come <em>before</em> a call to the XLPage() function in <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Internationalizations'>international wikis</a>.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>Save your config.php file encoded as UTF-8 (NO BOM). That allows entry of UTF-8 encoded characters in it. Make sure your editor does support this, and test by adding some non-ANSI UTF-8 characters, to see them in the text editor <sup><a href='#notes'>1</a></sup>.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>With UTF-8 thus enabled you also got use of classes <em>rtl</em> and <em>ltr</em>, which offer setting of the text direction to right-to-left, or left-to-right. This is useful for inclusion of right-to-left scripts like Arabic, Farsi (Persian), Hebrew, Urdu and others. 
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h2>Enabling UTF-8 on existing wikis</h2>
<p>Currently, this is possible <em>only if your group and page </em>names<em>, as well as upload names, don&rsquo;t contain international characters</em>. The names of wiki pages are used as file names, and we don&rsquo;t have yet an easy way to rename the disk files.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>If your wiki doesn&rsquo;t have international page/file names, first <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Upgrades'>upgrade</a> to the latest PmWiki version. To enable UTF-8, add these lines near the beginning of config.php:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><pre> include_once(&ldquo;scripts/xlpage-utf-8.php&rdquo;);
 $DefaultPageCharset = array(&lsquo;&thinsp;&rsquo;=&gt;&rsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;1&rsquo;); # see below
</pre><p class='vspace'>These lines should come <em>before</em> a call to the XLPage() function in <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Internationalizations'>international wikis</a>.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>The <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/I18nVariables#DefaultPageCharset'><code class='varlink'>&#036;DefaultPageCharset</code></a> line is there to fix and correctly handle some pages with missing or wrong attributes, created by older PmWiki versions.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><ul><li>Most wikis in European languages are likely to be in the ISO-8859&ndash;1 encoding and should use:<br />  <code><a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/I18nVariables#DefaultPageCharset'><code class='varlink'>&#036;DefaultPageCharset</code></a> = array(&lsquo;&thinsp;&rsquo;=&gt;&rsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;1&rsquo;);</code>
</li><li>Wikis in Czech and Hungarian language are likely to be in the ISO-8859&ndash;2 encoding, they should use this line instead:<br />  <code> <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/I18nVariables#DefaultPageCharset'><code class='varlink'>&#036;DefaultPageCharset</code></a> = array(&lsquo;&thinsp;&rsquo;=&gt;&rsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;2&rsquo;, &lsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;1&rsquo;=&gt;&rsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;2&rsquo;); </code>
</li><li>Wikis in Turkish language are likely to be in the ISO-8859&ndash;9 encoding, they should use this line instead:<br />  <code> <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/I18nVariables#DefaultPageCharset'><code class='varlink'>&#036;DefaultPageCharset</code></a> = array(&lsquo;&thinsp;&rsquo;=&gt;&rsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;9&rsquo;, &lsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;1&rsquo;=&gt;&rsquo;ISO-8859&ndash;9&rsquo;); </code>
</li></ul><p class='vspace'>You should also delete the file <code> wiki.d/.pageindex</code>. This file contains a cache of links and words from your pages and is used for searches and pagelists. PmWiki will rebuild it automatically with the new encoding.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h2>Support for RTL right-to-left languages</h2>
<p>Languages like Arabic, Hebrew, Farsi (Persian), Urdu and others are written in script flowing from right to left. Classes <em>rtl</em> and <em>ltr</em> can be used to specify direction of text independently of the general text direction within a page, for example: 
</p><table class='markup vert' align='center'>
      <tr><td class='markup1' valign='top'><pre>&gt;&gt;rtl&lt;&lt;
يتدفق هذا النص من اليمين إلى اليسار
&gt;&gt;ltr&lt;&lt;
This text flows left to right.
&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;
</pre></td></tr><tr><td 
        class='markup2' valign='top'><div class='rtl' > 
<p>يتدفق هذا النص من اليمين إلى اليسار
</p></div><div class='ltr' > 
<p>This text flows left to right.
</p></div>
</td></tr></table>
<p class='vspace'>To set text direction for a wiki generally to RTL, you could add to config.php a line like:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><pre>  <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/LayoutVariables#HTMLStylesFmt'><code class='varlink'>&#036;HTMLStylesFmt</code></a>[&lsquo;rtl&rsquo;] = &ldquo; body { direction:rtl; }&rdquo;
</pre><p class='vspace'>but  the skin you use may need other modifications, for instance to swap the search box and the page actions to the other side etc. 
</p>
<p class='vspace'>Some skins have full support for RTL, see for instance <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Skins/Amber' rel='nofollow'>Amber</a>. 
</p>
<p class='vspace'><a name='notes' id='notes'></a>
</p><h2>Notes</h2>
<ul><li>You need to save your config.php file in the UTF-8 encoding, and &ldquo;Without Byte Order Mark (BOM)&rdquo;. See <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/LocalCustomizations#encoding'>Character encoding of config.php</a>.
<div class='vspace'></div></li><li>This page concerns the most recent versions of PmWiki. See <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Cookbook/UTF-8' rel='nofollow'>Cookbook:UTF-8</a> for tips on older versions.
<div class='vspace'></div></li><li>In the case your pmwiki installation displays wrong encoding, or save an UTF-8 page to an other encoding without explanation, you can double check your custom .htaccess settings at the root of your served pages.
</li></ul><p class='vspace'> 
<a name='trailend' id='trailend'></a>
<br clear='all' />
</p><div  style='background-color: #ffe; border-top: 1px solid black; font-size: .8em;' > 
<p>This page may have <span class='commentout-pmwikiorg'> a more recent version on <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org' rel='nofollow'>pmwiki.org</a>: <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/PmWiki/UTF-8' rel='nofollow'>PmWiki:UTF-8</a>, and </span> a talk page: <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/PmWiki/UTF-8-Talk' rel='nofollow'>PmWiki:UTF-8-Talk</a>.
</p></div>
</div>

      </td>
    </tr></table>
